## Typography System and Hierarchy

### Font Family Specifications

- **Primary Interface Font**: Open Sans (digital screens, EHR interfaces) 
- **Clinical Documentation**: Arial (professional standard, regulatory compliance) 
- **Patient Communications**: Verdana (accessibility optimized, visual impairments) 
- **Fallback Stack**: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif

### Typography Scale and Hierarchy

- **H1 (Page Titles)**: 32px/1.25, font-weight: 600, color: –hc-text-primary
- **H2 (Section Headers)**: 24px/1.3, font-weight: 600, color: –hc-text-primary
- **H3 (Subsection Headers)**: 20px/1.4, font-weight: 500, color: –hc-text-primary
- **H4 (Component Headers)**: 18px/1.4, font-weight: 500, color: –hc-text-secondary
- **Body Text (Clinical)**: 16px/1.5, font-weight: 400, color: –hc-text-primary
- **Body Text (Secondary)**: 14px/1.5, font-weight: 400, color: –hc-text-secondary
- **Caption/Labels**: 12px/1.4, font-weight: 500, color: –hc-text-tertiary

### Healthcare-Specific Typography Guidelines

- **Minimum font size**: 14px for all clinical data and patient information  
- **Line height**: 1.4-1.6 for optimal medical text readability 
- **Character spacing**: Adequate kerning for medical terminology display
- **Accessibility**: Font size scaling support (100%, 125%, 150%, 200%)
- **Critical information emphasis**: Bold weight (600) for vital signs, alerts, patient identifiers

