## Iconography and Visual Elements

### Medical Icon System

**Primary Healthcare Icons (24x24px SVG):**

- **Vital Signs**: Heart (pulse), thermometer (temperature), lungs (respiration), gauge (BP)
- **Medical Specialties**: Stethoscope (general), brain (neurology), heart (cardiology)
- **Clinical Actions**: Prescription pad (medications), calendar (appointments), notes (documentation)
- **Status Indicators**: Alert triangle, checkmark (completed), clock (pending), warning

**Icon Implementation Standards:**

- **SVG format**: Scalable, crisp rendering, accessibility support
- **Consistent stroke width**: 2px for 24x24 icons, scalable for larger sizes
- **Square viewBox**: Values divisible by 8 for pixel-perfect rendering 
- **Semantic markup**: Proper ARIA labels and role definitions
- **Cultural sensitivity**: Universally recognizable medical symbols  

### Visual Design Elements

**Healthcare-Appropriate Visual Patterns:**

- **Status badges**: Rounded rectangles with high contrast text
- **Progress indicators**: Clinical timeline visualization, treatment completion tracking
- **Data visualization**: Line charts (vital signs), bar charts (lab values), gauge charts (KPIs)  
- **Photo integration**: Patient photos with privacy controls, provider headshots
- **Document previews**: PDF thumbnails, lab report previews, imaging study snapshots

**Visual Hierarchy Techniques:**

- **Card elevation**: Subtle shadows for information grouping
- **Color coding**: Consistent status colors across all components
- **Typography emphasis**: Bold weight for critical information, regular for supporting details
- **White space utilization**: 42% neutral space for cognitive breathing room 
